%description
Point and interval estimation in dual frame surveys. In contrast to
classic sampling theory, where only one sampling frame is considered, dual
frame methodology assumes that there are two frames available for sampling
and that, overall, they cover the entire target population. Then, two
probability samples (one from each frame) are drawn and information
collected is suitably combined to get estimators of the parameter of
interest.

